th; they refer to the 六尘, 六根, 六识, and 七大; disciples of the Buddha are said each to have acquired a special knowledge of one of these twenty-five and to have been recognized as its authority, e. g. Guanyin of the ear, Dignga of sound, etc.Tiantai's twenty-five aids to meditation, v. 止观.The twenty-five forms of existence, fourteen in the desire realms 欲界, seven in the realms of form 色界, and four in the formless realms 无色界, v. 有.The monk's twenty-five-patch garment, v. 袈.Each of the five 更 night watches is divided into five making twenty-five dian.The twenty-five guardian deities who protect any keeper of the commandments, i.e. five for each of the commandments against killing, robbing, adultery, lying, and drinking.The twenty-five bodhisattvas who protect all who call on Amitbha i. e. 观音, 大势至, 药王, 药上, 普贤, 法自在, 师子吼, 陀罗尼, 虚空藏, 佛藏, 菩藏, 金藏, 金刚藏, 山海慧, 光明王, 华严王, 宾王, 月光王, 日照王, 三昧王, 定自在王, 大自在王, 自象王, 大威德王 and 无边身菩萨.Sroakovia. Defined as the most zealous of kyamuni's disciples, who became an arhat. Having lived in a heaven for ninety-one kalpas, where his feet did not touch the ground, he was born with hair on his soles two inches long, an omen which led his father and brothers to endow him with twenty <foreign lang="sa">koti</foreign>s of ounces of gold, hence this name. v. 智度论 22.The twenty-eight heavens, or devalokas: six of the desire-world 欲界, eighteen of the form-world 色界, and four arpa or formless heavens 无色界. The heavens of the world of form are sixteen according to the 萨婆多部 Sarvstivda School, seventeen according to 经部 Stra School, and eighteen according to the 上座 Sthavir.The twenty-eight <foreign lang="sa">nakatra</foreign>s or constellations, divided into four mansions of seven each, referred to East, or Spring; South, Summer; West, Autumn; and North, Winter. The month-names derived from them differ slightly in form. E.: 角 Citr, 亢 Niy (or Svti), 氏 Vikh, 房 Anurdh, 心Rohi, Jyehaghn (or Jyesth), 尾 Mlabarha (or Mla), 箕 Prva-Adha. N.: 斗 Uttara-Ah, 牛 Abhijit, 女rava, 卢raviha 