e of kyamuni, who was in a former life Vimaladatt. ' Eitel.The auspicious ray sent from between the Buddha's eyebrows before a revelation.The bright-eyed (or wide-eyed) daughter, a former incarnation of 地藏 Kitigarbha.Guang the general supervisor, i. e. the monk 慧光 Huiguang, sixth century, who resigned the high office of 统 and tr. the 十地经论.Jlinprabhakumra, 惹哩宁罗婆摩罗; one of the eight attendants on Majur; he is the youth with the shining net.one of the five 佛顶 q. v.The above-mentioned 舍论记 in 30 <foreign lang="zh">juan</foreign> by 普光 Puguang, v. 光.To turn the light inwards on oneself, concern oneself with one's own duty.Mahkyapy, or school of the Mahsghika.The honoured one descends, i. e. the Buddha or bodhisattva who is worshipped descends.bhsvara, light and sound, or light-sound heavens, also styled 极光净天, the heavens of utmost light and purity, i. e. the third of the second <foreign lang="sa">dhyna</foreign> heavens, in which the inhabitants converse by light instead of words; they recreate the universe from the hells up to and including the first <foreign lang="sa">dhyna</foreign> heavens after it has been destroyed by fire during he final series of cataclysms; but they gradually diminish in power and are reborn in lower states. The three heavens of the second <foreign lang="sa">dhyna</foreign> are 少光, 无量光, and 光音.bhsvara-vimna, the bhsvara palace, idem.Avoid; remit.A monk whose attendance at the daily assembly is excused for other duties.Helmet, hood; pocket, bag; translit. tu.The Tuita and the Yama heavens.A <foreign lang="sa">stpa</foreign>.路婆 ? <term lang="sa">turuka</term>; <foreign lang="la">
