vereign ruler.Devarja-tathgata, the name by which Devadatta, the enemy of kyamuni, will be known on his future appearance as a Buddha in the universe called 天道 Devasopna; his present residence in hell being temporary for his karmaic expurgation.<foreign lang="sa">deva</foreign> lines or pictures.idem天道.(天力士)  idem 那罗延 Narayana.Deva-king; the Tang monk 道悟 Daowu of the 天皇 Tianhuang monastery at 荆州 Jingzhou.A Buddha's canopy, or umbrella; a nimbus of rays of light, a halo.divyacakus. The <foreign lang="sa">deva</foreign>-eye; the first <foreign lang="sa">abhij</foreign>, v. 六通; one of the five classes of eyes; divine sight, unlimited vision; all things are open to it, large and small, near and distant, the destiny of all beings in future rebirths. It may be obtained among men by their human eyes through the practice of meditation 修得: and as a reward or natural possession by those born in the <foreign lang="sa">deva</foreign> heavens 报得. Cf 天耳, etc.The power of the celestial or <foreign lang="sa">deva</foreign> eye, one of the ten powers of a Buddha.One of the three enlightenments 三明, or clear visions of the saint, which enables him to know the future rebirths of himself and all beings.The wisdom obtained by the <foreign lang="sa">deva</foreign> eye.(天眼智通)  The complete universal knowledge and assurance of the <foreign lang="sa">deva</foreign> eye.The sixth of Amitbha's forty-eight vows, that he would not enter the final stage until all beings had obtained this divine vision.idem 天眼; also a term used by those who practise hypnotism.Tiandu, an erroneous form of 天竺, or 印度 Yindu, India.deva 提婆 or devat 泥缚多. (1) Brahma and the gods in general, including the inhabitants of the <foreign lang="sa">devaloka</foreign>s, all subject to metem-psychosis. (2) The fifteenth patriarch, a native of South India, or Ceylon and disciple of Ngrjuna; he is also styled Devabodhisattva 提婆菩萨, ryadeva 圣天, and Nilanetra 目 blue-eyed, or 分别明 clear discriminator. He was the author of nine works and