inally returned into his mouth.The state or condition of a Tathgata.The abode of the Tathgata, i. e. 慈悲 mercy, or pity.The Tathgata is eternal, always abiding.Tathgata, Worshipful, Omniscient-three titles of a Buddha.怛他蘖多母隶底多 The seventh Bodhisattva to the right of kyamuni in the Garbhadhtu group, in charge of the pity or sympathy of the Tathgata. There are other bodhisattvas in charge of other Tathgata forms or qualities in the same group.相日 The Tathgata day, which is without beginning or end and has no limit of past, present, or future.如来寿量品 Chapters in the <title>Lotus Sutra</title> on Tathgata powers and eternity.The play of the Tathgata, i. e. the exercise of his manifold powers.tathgata-garbha, the Tathgata womb or store, defined as (1) the 如 <foreign lang="zh">zhenru</foreign>, q. v. in the midst of 烦恼 the delusion of passions and desires; (2) sutras of the Buddha's uttering. The first especially refers to the <foreign lang="zh">zhenru</foreign> as the source of all things: whether compatibles or incompatibles, whether forces of purity or impurity, good or bad, all created things are in the Tathgatagarbha, which is the womb that gives birth to them all. The second is the storehouse of the Buddha's teaching.idem 如心.The natures of all the living are the nature of the Tathgata; for which v. the 如来藏经, 如来藏论, etc.<term lang="sa">tathgata-kya</term>, Buddha-body.The court of Vairocana Tathgata in the Garbhadhtu group.like a dream.
