Satyasiddhi sect, based on the 成实论 <title>Satyasiddhi-stra</title>,
tr. by Kumrajva; no sect corresponds to it in India; in China and Japan it
became incorporated in the 三论宗. (3) 律宗 Vinaya or Discipline sect, based
on 十诵律, 四分律, 僧祗律, etc. (4) 三论宗 The three <foreign lang="sa">stra</foreign> sect, based on the
<title>Mdhyamika-stra</title> 中观论 of Ngrjuna, the
<title>Sata-stra</title> 百论 of ryadeva, and the
<title>Dvdasa-nikya-stra</title> 十二门论 of Ngrjuna; this school
dates back to the translation of the three <foreign lang="sa">stra</foreign>s by Kumrajva in A. D. 409. (5) 涅盘宗 Nirva
sect, based upon the <title>Mahparinirva-stra</title> 涅盘经 tr. by
Dharmaraksa in 423; later incorporated in Tiantai, with which it had much in
common. (6) 地论宗 Daabhmik sect, based on Vasubandhu's work on the ten
