Rhula, the eldest son of kyamuni and Yaodhar; also罗; 罗吼; 罗云; 罗云; 曷怙罗 or 何怙罗 or 罗怙罗. He is supposed to have been in the womb for six years and born when his father attained buddhahood; also said to have been born during an eclipse, and thus acquired his name, though it is defined in other ways; his father did not see him till he was six years old. He became a disciple of the Hnayna, but is said to have become a Mahynist when his father preached this final perfect doctrine, a statement gainsaid by his being recognized as founder of the Vaibhika school. He is to be reborn as the eldest son of every buddha, hence is sometimes called the son of nanda.Rhulatta, of Kapila, the sixteenth Patriarch, "who miraculously transported himself to the kingdom of rvast, where he saw on the Hirayavat the shadow of five Buddhas"; a sage, Saghanandi, was there in meditation and him he appointed as his successor.Prayga, now Allahabad.v. 般 <term lang="sa">praj</term>.<term lang="sa">prastha</term>, a weight tr. as a 斤 Chinese pound; a measure.<term lang="sa">ravaa</term>, clamorous, demanding.Rjagha, v. 罗阅.<term lang="sa">rj</term>, a queen, a princess.Kaukkuik is described as one of the eighteen schools of Hnayna; cf. 拘; 鸠; 窟; 居.<term lang="sa">brhmaa</term>, v. 婆罗门.Rjagha, also 罗阅只 (罗阅只迦罗); 罗阅耆; 罗阅揭黎醯; 罗越; 罗惹讫哩□ The capital of Magadha, at the foot of the Gdhraka mountain, first metropolis of Buddhism and seat of the first synod; v. 王舍.Rhu-<foreign lang="sa">asura</foreign>, the <foreign lang="sa">asura</foreign> who in fighting with Indra can seize sun and moon, i.e. cause eclipses.(罗陀那) <term lang="sa">ratna</term>, anything precious, a gem, etc.; also 罗怛那 or 罗怛曩 or 罗怛囊. Cf.  and 七.Cease, stop; mark of finality.To dismiss the assembly.That which is blameworthy and brings about bad karma; entangled in the net of wrong-doing; sin, crime.That which sin does, its karma, producing subsequent suffering.The filth of sin, moral defilement.Sins, crimes.A sinful nature; the nature of sin.Sin and