difference, it was predicted that he would become a disciple of Buddha.Kaaptana, a kind of ill-smelling demon, a <foreign lang="sa">preta</foreign> in the lower regions. M.W.'Khadiraka, the third of the seven circles around Meru. Cf. □.(羯尼迦) <term lang="sa">kanaka</term>, gold; name of several yellow plants, e.g. thorn apple; <foreign lang="la">
Butea frondosa</foreign>; a species of sandalwood, etc.<term lang="sa">karpra</term>, dragon-brain scent, camphor.Karma, v. 业 and cf. 羯磨.(羯毗迦罗) <term lang="sa">kalavika</term>, v. 迦.Krakucchanda, v. 迦.<term lang="sa">karma</term>; action, work, deed, performance, service, 'duty'; religious action, moral duty; especially a meeting of the monks for the purpose of ordination, or for the confession of sins and absolution, or for expulsion of the unrepentant. There are numerous kinds of karma, or assemblies for such business, ordinarily requiring the presence of four monks, but others five, ten, or twenty. Cf. 业 for definition of karma, deeds or character as the cause of future conditions; also 五蕴 for karma as the fourth <foreign lang="sa">skandha</foreign>.An assembly for monastic duty; also the central group of the Vajradhtu <foreign lang="sa">maala</foreign>.A monastic assembly; also a monk on duty, e.g. in meditation.An image showing the symbol of a <foreign lang="sa">bodhisattva</foreign>'s activity.An image, a term used by the esoterics.<term lang="sa">karmadna</term>, i.e. the 维那 or director of duties.Karasuvara. 'An ancient kingdom in Gundwana, the region about Gangpoor, Lat. 21 54 N., Long. 84 30 E.' Eitel.<term lang="sa">kalaa</term>, a water-pot, pitcher, jar, dish, also 迦罗舍; 羯.cf. 羯陵. For Krakucchanda, v. 迦.or 羯腊缚 <term lang="sa">karaphu</term>, or <term lang="sa">kalahu</term>, 'a particularly high number' (M.W.), 10 quintillions; 大羯腊婆 100 quintillions; cf. 洛叉.Kanyakubja, 'hump-backed maidens.' An ancient city and kingdom of Central India. In antiquity this city ranks next to Ayodhy in Oudh. It is known to classical geography as Canogyza. The etymology refers to the legend of the hundred daughters of Kuanbha its king, who refused the licentious desires of Vyu (Mahvka 大树仙) and were turned by him into hunchbacks. M.W. Eitel says 'the modem Canouge'.Kajighara, Kajangala, or Kajghira; a kingdom whose ruling family was extinct in A.D. 400.' The ruins of the capital are situated at the village of Kadjri near Farakhabad (Lat. 27 24 N., Long. 7927 E.) in the province of Agra.' Eitel. Also 羯殊祗罗.Khadrira 羯陀罗; v. 竭.<term lang="sa">kalala</term>, the human embryo during the first seven days; the womb; also 羯罗蓝, 歌罗逻, etc.<term lang="sa">khaika</term>. Lictors in hades; possibly from the root <foreign lang="sa">khd</foreign>, to devour; also 羯罗; 伽□那; it is also defined as 'dog-cookers', butchers, hunters, those who live by killing and selling animals, persons of very low caste.Kaliga, also 羯M044209伽. An ancient kingdom south-east of Koala, a nursery of heretical sects, the present Kalingapatnam. Eitel. Also with 羯罗频迦 used for <foreign lang="sa">kalavika</foreign>, v. 迦.Kaanna. 'An ancient kingdom 300 <foreign lang="zh">li</foreign> south-west of Kharismiga on the Oxus, the present Koorshee' Karshi. Eitel.Crowding sheep, confusion; translit. <foreign lang="sa">kan</foreign>, <foreign lang="sa">an</foreign>.(or羼提) <term lang="sa">knti</term>, patience, forbearance, enduring shame, one of the six <foreign lang="sa">pramit</foreign>s.Kntii, name of kyamuni in a previous incarnation, the patient or enduring <foreign lang="sa">i</foreign>.<term lang="sa">aila</term>, a sterile woman, cf. 扇.A wing, fin; translit. <foreign lang="sa">ke</foreign>.Feather robes.枳翅罗; 吉翅 <term lang="sa">keyra</term>, an armlet, necklace.<term lang="sa">keakambala</term>, a hair garment or covering; name of one of the ten heretical Indian schools.A film; screen; fan; hide, invisible; translit. <foreign lang="sa">e</foreign>, <foreign lang="sa">a</foreign>.Elpattra, a <foreign lang="sa">nga</foreign> who is said to have consulted kyamuni about rebirth in a higher sphere; also, a palm-tree formerly destroyed by that <foreign lang="sa">nga</foreign>.A drug for making the body invisible.<term lang="sa">eka</term>, one, once, single, unique.翻 To translate, interpret.To translate from Sanskrit.To translate the scriptures.To translate, interpret.<title>Fan yi ming yi j