s Vigila, Vikila, Varagala; the ancient capital of Andhra, cf. 案; but it is doubtful.Jina, victor, he who overcomes, a title of every Buddha; also the name of various persons; the Jaina religion, the Jains.To endure, bear.The patience which endures enmity and injury.Narmad, the modern Nerbudda river.<term lang="sa">rotra</term>, the ear, one of the 六根 six organs of sense, hence 耳入 is one of the twelve 入, as 耳处 is one of the twelve 处.<term lang="sa">rotrendriya</term>, the organ of hearing.<term lang="sa">rotravijna</term>. Ear-perception, ear-discernment.Secret rules whispered in the ear, an esoteric practice.An ear-ring.An interrogative particle; translit. for <foreign lang="sa">jha</foreign>, <foreign lang="sa">ya</foreign>.<term lang="sa">yava</term>, barely; a barleycorn, the 2,688,000th part of <foreign lang="sa">yojana</foreign>; also a measure in general of varying weight and length.Avalokitevara cf. 观音.Yavana, Yavadvpa, i. e. Java.耶维 cf 荼毗 <term lang="sa">jhpita</term>, cremation.Yaas, or 耶舍陀 Yaoj. There were two persons of this name: (1) a disciple of nanda; (2) another who is said to have 'played an important part in connection with the second synod'.(耶输陀); 耶输多罗. 耶戍达罗 Yaodhar; the wife of kyamuni, mother of Rhula, who became a nun five years after her husband's enlightenment. She is to become the Buddha Rami-ata-sahasra-paripra-dhvaja; v. <title>Lotus Sutra</title>. Her name was also Gop, 瞿波; 劬毗那 is perhaps Gop.To record, oversee, direct; office, official duty.Duty, responsibility.Connected, linked.<term lang="sa">samsa</term> ; assemble, collect; an assemblage.The phenomenal world likened to assembled scum, or bubbles.<term lang="sa">samudaya</term>, the second of the four dogmas, that of 'accumulation', i.e. that suffering is caused by the passions.To assemble, flock together.Quick at hearing, sharp, clever, astute, wise, 聪明.Wise, clever.To begin, initiate.or 僧肇 Sengzhao, name of a monk in the fourth century whose treatise is called by this name.<term lang="sa">msa</term>. Flesh.肉团心; 纥利陀耶 <term lang="sa">hdaya</term>; the physical heart.肉香 To cremate oneself alive as a lamp or as incense for Buddha.<term lang="sa">msacakus</term>. Eye of flesh, the physical eye.Flesh-coloured, red.One who becomes a bodhisattva in the physical body, in the present life.The physical body.<term lang="sa">msabhakaa</term>, meat-eating.鸟失尼沙; 郁失尼沙; 鸟瑟尼沙; 郁瑟尼沙; 鸟瑟
