ence known as Upatiya; noted for his wisdom and learning; he is the "right-hand attendant on kyamuni". The followers of the Abhidharma count him as their founder and other works are attributed, without evidence, to him. He figures prominently in certain sutras. He is said to have died before his master; he is represented as standing with Maudgalyyana by the Buddha when entering nirvana. He is to reappear as Padmaprabha Buddha 华光佛.<foreign lang="sa">aka</foreign>, 舍吒迦; 舍那 (or 奢那) An inner garment, a skirt.The state of renunciation, or indifference to sensation.M077447 舍□ <foreign lang="sa">stdevamanuym</foreign>, intp. as 天人师 teacher of gods and men, one of the ten titles of a buddha.atabhi, a constellation identified with 危 in Aquarius.rdla-kara. The original name of nanda, intp. 虎耳 tiger's ears.? kya, one of the five surnames of the Buddha.v. 舍.The Abhidharma or Piaka School.To leave home and cast off desire, i.e. to become a monk.The mind of renunciation.The pure land or heaven free from thinking, the fifth of the nine <foreign lang="sa">brahmaloka</foreign>s in the fourth <foreign lang="sa">dhyna</foreign> region.<foreign lang="sa">ama</foreign>, calm, quiet, a name for the bodhi tree. For舍摩陀 v. 奢.<term lang="sa">aa</term>, 设施 a hare; <term lang="sa">a</term>, or <term lang="sa">ain</term>, the moon; <term lang="sa">akti</term>, energy. (1) The hare (which threw itself into the fire to save starving people), transferred by Indra to the centre of the moon. (2) <foreign lang="sa">akti</foreign> is the wife or female energy of a deity, cf. 舍脂. (3) The female organ.<term lang="sa">upek</term>, one of the four forms of the unsparing or unlimited mind, complete abandonment, absolute indifference, renunciation of the mental faculties.<foreign lang="sa">luka</foreign>, esculent lotus roots; intp. as a kind of cooked liquid food.<term lang="sa">mana</term>, a cemetery or crematorium; a low mound of stone under which the remains of monks are buried in countries west of Chi