n lang="sa">cakravart</foreign> ruling over one continent, the south; the copper, over two, east and south: the silver, over three, east, west, and south; the golden being supreme over all the four continents. The term is also applied to the gods over a universe, and to a buddha as universal spiritual king, and as preacher of the supreme doctrine. Only a <foreign lang="sa">cakravart</foreign> possesses the 七 <foreign lang="sa">saptaratna</foreign> and 1, 000 sons. The <foreign lang="sa">cakra</foreign>, or discus, is also a missile used by a <foreign lang="sa">cakravart</foreign> for overthrowing his enemies. Its origin is probably the sun with its myriad rays.To reject the illusion of the transmigrational worlds and enter into nirvana-enlightenment.The two wheels of a cart compared by the Tiantai school to 定 (or to its Tiantai form 止观) and 慧 meditation and wisdom; see 止观 5. Also 食 food and 法 the doctrine, i. e. food physical and spiritual.
